## WebSocket Testing Strategy

### Backend WebSocket Tests

```go
func TestWebSocketHub_Broadcast_DeliversToAllClients(t *testing.T) {
    hub := NewHub()
    go hub.Run()
    
    // Create mock clients
    client1 := newMockClient(hub)
    client2 := newMockClient(hub)
    
    // Register clients
    hub.Register <- client1
    hub.Register <- client2
    
    // Broadcast message
    hub.Broadcast <- []byte(`{"event":"message.new","data":{}}`)
    
    // Assert both clients received the message
    assert.Eventually(t, func() bool {
        return client1.ReceivedCount() == 1 && client2.ReceivedCount() == 1
    }, time.Second, 10*time.Millisecond)
}
```

### Frontend WebSocket Tests (MSW)

```typescript
import { setupServer } from 'msw/node';
import { ws } from 'msw';

const server = setupServer(
  ws.link('ws://localhost:8080/ws').addEventListener('connection', ({ client }) => {
    client.addEventListener('message', (event) => {
      // Mock server response
      client.send(JSON.stringify({ event: 'message.ack', data: { status: true } }));
    });
  })
);
```

## Database Testing (PostgreSQL)

### Use Testcontainers for Integration Tests

```go
func setupTestDB(t *testing.T) *sql.DB {
    ctx := context.Background()
    
    container, err := postgres.RunContainer(ctx,
        testcontainers.WithImage("postgres:15"),
        postgres.WithDatabase("byteroom_test"),
        postgres.WithUsername("test"),
        postgres.WithPassword("test"),
    )
    require.NoError(t, err)
    
    t.Cleanup(func() {
        container.Terminate(ctx)
    })
    
    connStr, err := container.ConnectionString(ctx, "sslmode=disable")
    require.NoError(t, err)
    
    db, err := sql.Open("postgres", connStr)
    require.NoError(t, err)
    
    // Run migrations
    runMigrations(db)
    
    return db
}
```

## API Contract Testing

### Define Contracts First

```yaml
# api/openapi.yaml
paths:
  /api/messages/{chatId}:
    get:
      summary: Get chat history
      responses:
        200:
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: '#/components/schemas/MessageList'
```

### Generate Types and Validate

```bash
# Generate Go types from OpenAPI
oapi-codegen -generate types -package api api/openapi.yaml > internal/api/types.gen.go

# Generate TypeScript types
npx openapi-typescript api/openapi.yaml -o src/api/types.ts
```

## Pre-Commit Hooks

### Required Checks Before Commit

```yaml
# .pre-commit-config.yaml
repos:
  - repo: local
    hooks:
      - id: go-tests
        name: Go Tests
        entry: go test ./... -short
        language: system
        pass_filenames: false
        
      - id: frontend-tests
        name: Frontend Tests
        entry: npm test -- --run
        language: system
        pass_filenames: false
```

## CI/CD Test Pipeline

```yaml
# .github/workflows/test.yml
name: Test Suite

on: [push, pull_request]

jobs:
  backend-tests:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-go@v5
        with:
          go-version: '1.22'
      - name: Run Unit Tests
        run: go test ./... -short -coverprofile=coverage.out
      - name: Run Integration Tests
        run: go test ./... -tags=integration

  frontend-tests:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
      - run: npm ci
      - name: Run Tests
        run: npm run test:coverage
```

## Exit Criteria for Each Feature

Before marking any feature as "Done", verify:

- [ ] All acceptance tests pass
- [ ] Unit test coverage ≥ 80%
- [ ] Integration tests for external dependencies
- [ ] No failing tests in CI pipeline
- [ ] Code reviewed and approved
- [ ] Documentation updated

## Quick Reference

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Run Go unit tests | `go test ./... -short` |
| Run Go integration tests | `go test ./... -tags=integration` |
| Go coverage report | `go test ./... -coverprofile=coverage.out && go tool cover -html=coverage.out` |
| Run frontend tests | `npm run test` |
| Frontend watch mode | `npm run test:watch` |
| Frontend coverage | `npm run test:coverage` |
